## UI fixup: regressions from the all-white sweep (slider track + graph chat)

**Context**: After the grey‚Üíwhite sweep above, two regressions surfaced (verified against the
running dev server on `:8000`): (1) the Knowledge Graph **Depth slider** track became invisible,
and (2) the **Graph Chat** panel kept a grey gradient background. The home-page report ("sections
still grey") was a stale browser cache ‚Äî `curl :8000/static/global/css/main.css` confirmed
`--db-light-gray: #FFFFFF` is served, so the home tiles (`.stat-item` / `.info-card` /
`.domain-btn` / `.quick-link*` / `.domain-status`, all `var(--db-light-gray)`) already render
white; the `?v=asset_version` cache-buster only changes on server restart.

**Changes**:
1. `src/front/static/global/css/main.css` ‚Äî removed the global `--bs-secondary-bg` and
   `--bs-tertiary-bg` white overrides. Bootstrap's `.form-range` track and disabled-control
   surfaces read `--bs-secondary-bg`, so whitening it hid the slider line on the white page.
   Kept `--bs-light` / `--bs-light-rgb` white (drives `.bg-light` utilities to white, which the
   sweep intended); all `var(--bs-tertiary-bg, ‚Ä¶)` background usages were already flattened to
   literal `#ffffff` in the sweep, so dropping that override is background-safe. Added a comment
   documenting why these two tokens must not be whitened.
2. `src/front/static/query/css/query-chat.css` ‚Äî `--gc-panel-bg` changed from
   `linear-gradient(180deg, #f8fafc 0%, #eef2f7 100%)` to `#ffffff`. The original sweep only
   matched `background` / `background-color` declarations, so this grey lived in a CSS custom
   property and slipped through. `--gc-bot-border: #e9ecef` is a border and was left intact.

**Modified files**:
- `src/front/static/global/css/main.css`
- `src/front/static/query/css/query-chat.css`

**Test result**: CSS-only change; no new lint errors. Verified live via
`curl :8000/static/...` that the served CSS no longer overrides `--bs-secondary-bg` (slider track
visible again) and that the chat panel background is `#ffffff`. Browser hard-refresh / dev-server
restart needed to bust the cached `?v=` stylesheet.

